  "notes": "This ontology is designed to support multi-venture scenarios where individuals hold multiple roles across different organizations. It properly separates INDIVIDUALS (who fill roles), USERS (who access systems), and ROLES (organizational positions). RACI applies to ROLES for accountability, while RBAC governs USERS through role-inherited permissions. Schema.org alignment is intentionally 71% as governance concepts (RACI, RBAC) extend beyond schema.org scope."
